extends layout

block contents
    .article
        h3 In-browser solution to encrypt text messages by&nbsp;
          a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Encryption_Standard",target="_new",rel="nofollow") Advanced Encryption Standard (AES)
        center
          iframe(width="560", height="315", src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ItTkczs_cRA", frameborder="0", allowfullscreen)
        p &nbsp;

        p Encrypting email with Encipher.it is a simple way to protect your sensitive data. You can encrypt emails with your private info and only the recipient can decrypt it with correct password. To deal with email encryption you have to type the message in Gmail or any other email web service, click on Encipher It button and create a password. In the same way you can encrypt messages in Facebook or any other social networks and web services. You need only to enter your message in a text field, use bookmarklet and type a password to encrypt message.
    h1 How to install
    .line
    #install.article
        h2 1. Add bookmark
        .line
        .articleBody.clear
            .figure1
                img(src="/images/step1.png")
             p 
                b Firefox or Google Chrome:
                br
                span Drag this link: &nbsp;
                a(href=def_bookmarklet)
                    b Encipher It
                span &nbsp;&nbsp; to your Bookmarks Bar

            p
                b Internet Explorer:
                br
                span Right click: &nbsp;
                a(href=def_bookmarklet)
                    b Encipher It
                span &nbsp; and click "Add to Favorites"
            p
                b Apple Devices
                br
                a(href="/ios") Please use iOS version
    .article
        h2 2. Encrypt message
        .line 
        .articleBody.clear
            .figure
                img(src="/images/step2.png", width="500")
            p
                span Login to 
                b Google Mail, 
                b Facebook 
                span or other site where you want to protect the text. 
            p Type your message and click the bookmark.
            p Enter the password and click the "Encrypt" button. 


    .article
        h2 3. Decrypt message
        .line 
        .articleBody.clear
            .figure
                img(src="/images/step3.png", width="500")
            p To decrypt the message on the page, just click bookmark again and reenter the same password.

    h1 How It Works
    .line 
    #how.article
        .articleBody.clear
            p 
              a(href=def_bookmarklet) Encipher It
              | &nbsp;is javascript code snippet. It can be injected to any web page by clicking on the bookmark.
              | It ask for the password, generate secure key and encrypt or decrypt the text on the web page.
              | Optionally, it can save encrypted text on the external server and provide short link for access.
            p
              | We use&nbsp;
              a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Encryption_Standard",target="_new",rel="nofollow") AES
              | &nbsp;encryption with&nbsp;
              a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PBKDF2", target="new", rel="nofollow") PBKDF2
              | &nbsp;key generation and&nbsp;
              a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hash-based_message_authentication_code", target="new", rel="nofollow") HMAC-SHA256
              | &nbsp;digests.
            p
              | The plain text and the key is managed inside browser memory and never passed by network.
              | However, encryption code still loaded from the server. Be aware of &nbsp;
              a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man-in-the-middle_attack",rel="nofollow") man-in-the-middle 
              |  and 
              a(href="phishing") phising
              |  attacks.
              | For the safe use, ensure that site address is exactly&nbsp;
              b &nbsp;&nbsp; https://encipher.it &nbsp;&nbsp;
              | &nbsp;("https" important!). If you see red alert, please stop using this tool and send me a note.
            p
              | The source code is available on&nbsp;
              a(href="https://github.com/ermakus/encipher.it") GitHub
